Cell.Text: [S] All the mages are up in the College. You can ask them, if they'll let you in. | Then again, maybe Nelacar would know. He's a long-term guest here. Knows a few spells. I think he was at the College a long time ago.
[S] Did you say an "elf" and "stars"? I hope you don't know what you're asking.
[S] "An elf that studies stars"? Where did you hear about that?
[S] Studies stars you say? Why, there hasn't been a mage doing anything related to stars since.... Oh....
[S] Why specifically stars? Wait, you aren't referring to... No, there's no way would would know about that.
[S] I know plenty of spells that produce light, but stars? Hmm. There was that problem a few years ago, but that couldn't be related.
[S] Stars? You wouldn't be referring to that incident a few years ago? I still say that exile was far too harsh.
[S] Why would anyone bother to study stars? Well, unless you're talking about that artifact that got all those... dimwits thrown out.
[S] Studies stars? I remember the last time the word "stars" was flown through the Hall of the Elements. Bad things had happened.

Node.Caption: DA01CollegeQuestionsBranchTopic: Is there an elven mage here that studies stars?

Cell.Text: [S] There was an... unfortunate incident a few years ago. An elven mage named Nelacar was exiled from the College over it. | He's still in town, getting by plying spells to the people inside the Frozen Hearth. Disgraceful.
[S] Officially, nothing. | Why don't you head into town and get a drink at the Frozen Hearth? I hear old Nelacar still has a room there. He knows a lot of stories, that one.

[S] Well, it's a... minor stain on the College's reputation. One of many, unfortunately. | You should head to the Frozen Hearth and speak with Nelacar. It's his story to tell, and I wouldn't want to discredit him by talking behind his back.

[S] It was a few years ago. A few of the mages got overconfidant and were exiled. They had no talent, anyway. | I hear one of them, Nelacar, still hangs around the Frozen Hearth. Guess he has no where else to go, poor thing.

[S] There was some bother about a group of mages being exiled. I can't remember what the details were. | I think one of them came back. Nelacar. Stays at the Frozen Hearth, but I don't know why. He's not welcome in the College.
[S] You shouldn't ask me. There's an Altmer named Nelacar in the Frozen Hearth. He's the one to talk to.
"Dimwits"? What happened?

[S] Oh, no, I'm not falling for that one again. Next thing I know, I'm getting yelled at for saying something inappropriate. | If you're so curious, talk to Nelacar, in the Frozen Hearth. He can tell you the whole sad story.
What kind of things?

[S] The kind of things that even the College won't tolerate. Things that can get a wizard exiled for life. | There's an Altmer who's staying at the Frozen Hearth. Nelacar. You should speak with him, if you're so curious.

Node.Caption: DA01CollegeQuestionsTopic01: What is it? What happened?

Cell.Text: [S] Well, I've certainly heard worse things. | I think the man you want to talk to is Nelacar. He was exiled a few years ago, bad research. Still hangs around the Frozen Hearth.
[S] You were given a vision? Are you serious? | Whatever. The person you probably want is Nelacar. He's in the Frozen Hearth. Be careful, he was exiled from the College for a reason.
[S] No. I wouldn't. | Why don't you head into town and get a drink at the Frozen Hearth? I hear old Nelacar still has a room there. He knows a lot of stories, that one.
The vision is true, isn't it?

[S] Vision? What vision are you talking about? Oh, no matter. | You should head to the Frozen Hearth and speak with Nelacar. It's his story to tell, and I wouldn't want to discredit him by talking behind his back.
Something tells me that it is.
[S] You should go into town and talk to an elf named Nelacar. He was involved in the whole mess.
Did you say "exile"?
[S] Yes, I did. I shouldn't be the one to tell you about this. There's an Altmer named Nelacar in the Frozen Hearth. Believe me, he'll know.
Wait. What artifact?
[S] Oh no, I'm not talking about that. I'm not being blamed for saying something out of place. Again. | If you want to know, ask Nelacar. He's staying at the Frozen Hearth. Knows the whole sad story.
Is the College hiding something?
[S] Almost the opposite. The College got rid of something... someone, that was too much trouble. | There's an Altmer named Nelacar staying at the inn outside the College. You should ask him about it.

Node.Caption: DA01CollegeQuestionsTopic02: Would you believe I was given a vision?
